% Implement GitHub issue #820 â€” user stories as example-level contract coverage.
%
% Primary module: `pdd/user_story_tests.py` (extend; do not fork a parallel story generator).
% Authoring assets: `user_stories/story__template.md`, `README.md`, `docs/prompting_guide.md`.
%
% Tracker: https://github.com/promptdriven/pdd/issues/820
% Epic: https://github.com/promptdriven/pdd/issues/833

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Problem
PDD already discovers `user_stories/story__*.md`, validates them with `pdd detect --stories`,
and links prompts via `<!-- pdd-story-prompts: ... -->`. `contract_check` and
`coverage --contracts` already understand story `## Covers` references via `contract_ir`.
The on-disk template and programmatic story generator still use a minimal shape
(Story, Context, Acceptance Criteria, Non-Goals, Notes) and emit `## Prompt Scope`
instead of contract-aware sections. Authors lack a single source of truth that matches
the prompting guide and coverage tooling.

% Goal
Make user stories first-class **example-level coverage** for named contract rules without
breaking legacy stories. New templates and generated stories MUST teach the Covers /
Oracle / Non-Oracle / Negative Cases habit; validation MUST remain backward compatible.

<contract_rules>
R1 - Canonical template
The repository MUST ship `user_stories/story__template.md` containing, in order:
`## Covers`, `## Story`, `## Context`, `## Acceptance Criteria`, `## Oracle`,
`## Non-Oracle`, `## Negative Cases`, `## Non-Goals`, `## Notes`.
Placeholder text MUST match the issue #820 proposal (persona/behavior/value placeholders).

R2 - Generated story parity
When `generate_user_story()` / `_render_story_markdown_from_prompts()` runs (invoked from
`pdd test <*.prompt>` story mode via `pdd/commands/generate.py`), the written markdown MUST
include the same section headings as R1. The generator MUST NOT emit `## Prompt Scope`;
scope belongs in `## Context` and `<!-- pdd-story-prompts: ... -->`.

R3 - Covers seeding from prompts
When any input `.prompt` contains `<contract_rules>`, the generator MUST seed `## Covers`
with one bullet per rule ID using `parse_prompt_contracts()` from `pdd/contract_ir.py`:
format `- R{n}: <short rule summary>` (first line or trimmed obligation text, max 120 chars).
For multi-prompt generation, use cross-module Covers lines when multiple prompts contribute
rules: `prompts/<file>.prompt#R{n}: <summary>`.
When no `<contract_rules>` exist, emit a Covers section with a single placeholder bullet
instructing the author to add rule IDs after contracts are authored.

R4 - MUST NOT â†’ Negative Cases hint
When seeded rules include modal `MUST NOT`, the generator MUST add at least one bullet under
`## Negative Cases` naming the forbidden outcome (derived from rule text, not invented APIs).

R5 - Oracle / Non-Oracle defaults
The generator MUST emit non-empty starter bullets under `## Oracle` and `## Non-Oracle`
(issue examples: error type, state transition, external call presence, value shape;
non-oracle: helper names, internal structure, irrelevant ordering).
Do not call an LLM for story generation; remain deterministic.

R6 - Backward compatibility
`discover_story_files`, `cache_story_prompt_links`, `run_user_story_tests`, and
`run_user_story_fix` MUST NOT require the new sections. Missing sections MUST NOT fail
validation. Do not add hard failures in `user_story_tests.py` for absent Covers/Oracle.

R7 - Documentation alignment
`README.md` (user story section) and `docs/prompting_guide.md` MUST state that user stories
are example-level coverage for contract rules and point to `## Covers`.
Where the guide uses `## Forbidden Outcomes`, add a one-line note that issue #820 and the
on-disk template use `## Negative Cases` as the canonical heading (same intent).

R8 - Preservation
When editing `pdd/user_story_tests.py`, preserve existing comments, docstrings, and behavior
outside story rendering per issue #926. Keep lazy `change_main` import and `skip_user_stories`
hygiene unchanged.
</contract_rules>

<vocabulary>
- **Covers**: story `## Covers` bullets mapping rule IDs (R1, R2, or cross-module
  `prompts/foo.prompt#R3`) to human-readable obligation summaries.
- **Oracle**: observations that determine pass/fail for this story.
- **Non-Oracle**: details explicitly declared irrelevant to pass/fail.
- **Negative Cases**: forbidden outcomes the story protects against (especially MUST NOT rules).
- **Example-level coverage**: stories supplement tests; they are evidence for
  `pdd checkup coverage`, not a replacement for executable tests.
</vocabulary>

% Implementation requirements

1. **`user_stories/story__template.md`**
   Replace content with the canonical markdown below (exact headings for R1).

2. **`pdd/user_story_tests.py`**
   - Refactor `_render_story_markdown_from_prompts()` to build R1 sections.
   - Add `_seed_covers_from_prompts(prompt_paths: List[Path]) -> List[str]` using
     `parse_prompt_contracts` (handle missing file / no rules gracefully).
   - Add `_seed_negative_cases_from_rules(rules) -> List[str]` for R4.
   - Keep `_story_title_from_prompts`, metadata insertion, and post-write `detect_change`
     linking behavior intact.
   - Export nothing new unless tests need helpers; prefer private functions.

3. **Tests â€” `tests/test_user_story_tests.py`**
   - Update `test_generate_user_story_creates_story_file_and_links` expectations:
     assert `## Covers`, `## Oracle`, `## Non-Oracle`, `## Negative Cases` present;
     assert `## Prompt Scope` absent.
   - Add fixture prompt under `tests/fixtures/` with minimal `<contract_rules>` and assert
     Covers bullets reference R1/R2.
   - Add test that an existing minimal story file (no new sections) still passes
     `run_user_story_tests` when `detect_change` returns no changes.

4. **Docs**
   - README: 2â€“4 sentences on contract coverage + link to template and
     `docs/coverage_contracts.md` / `docs/contract_check.md`.
   - prompting_guide: reconcile Negative Cases vs Forbidden Outcomes per R7.

% Canonical template (write verbatim to `user_stories/story__template.md`)

```md
<!-- pdd-story-prompts: prompts/<module>_<language>.prompt -->

# User Story: <name>

## Covers

- R1: <contract rule name>
- R2: <contract rule name>

## Story

As a <persona>,
I want <behavior>,
so that <value>.

## Context

Describe relevant state, assumptions, fixtures, users, records, external services, or dependencies.

## Acceptance Criteria

1. Given ..., when ..., then ...
2. Given ..., when ..., then ...

## Oracle

These details matter for pass/fail:
- error type
- state transition
- absence/presence of external call
- emitted event
- returned value shape

## Non-Oracle

These details should not matter:
- private helper names
- internal class structure
- exact wording of non-user-facing messages
- deterministic but irrelevant ordering

## Negative Cases

List forbidden outcomes this story protects against.

## Non-Goals

What this story explicitly does not cover.

## Notes

Links, edge cases, fixtures, rationale, or implementation hints.
```

<acceptance_tests>
- `pytest tests/test_user_story_tests.py -q` MUST pass.
- `pdd detect --stories` against a repo using the new template sections MUST NOT regress
  (no new required sections enforced).
- `pdd test <prompt_with_contract_rules>.prompt` MUST write `user_stories/story__*.md` containing
  `## Covers`, `## Oracle`, `## Non-Oracle`, and `## Negative Cases`.
- A legacy `story__*.md` without those sections MUST still validate when `detect_change` is empty.
</acceptance_tests>

% Verification commands (run before finishing)
```bash
pytest -vv tests/test_user_story_tests.py
pylint pdd/user_story_tests.py
```

% Non-goals
- Do not require LLM story authoring.
- Do not change `detect_change` semantics or `contract_check` story parsers.
- Do not migrate every existing story file in the repo (template + generator only).
- Do not implement issue #821 (contract-aware `context/test.prompt`) in this change.

% Deliverables
- `user_stories/story__template.md`
- `pdd/user_story_tests.py`
- `tests/test_user_story_tests.py` (+ minimal fixture prompt if needed)
